cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.ET

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of soft information to improve the coding gain of a decoder, which is a key concept in information theory. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The implementation of the decoder involves the use of algorithms and data structures to efficiently process the incoming data. 
3. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper discusses the implementation of the decoder in a 28-nm technology, which is related to hardware architecture. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The use of soft information to improve the performance of the decoder can be seen as a control system problem. 
5. cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) - The use of soft information and energy-efficient design are both topics that fall under the umbrella of emerging technologies.
